Yes, they were not pieces of meat with fat but separate pieces of fat. It was extremely disturbing. The waiter has replaced the dish, the replacement didn't have separate pieces of fat, but was packed with salmon that has a thick layer of fat on it. On top of it all one piece had a salmon bone in it. It was clear that NON sushi grade fish was used for rolls (while sashimi were very high quality). Unfortunately the experience was too disturbing for us to come back. But if you go for Sashimi only, this place would be a good option.
